{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|串|心|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=heart}}.

Since ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' does not have the character {{och-l|*串}}, it interprets the character as {{Han compound|吅|丨|心|c1=p|c2=s|c3=s|t3=heart}} – to pierce through something from the heart. {{w|Duan Yucai}} claims in his commentary that older copies of ''Shuowen'' actually have {{Han compound|毌|心|c1=p|c2=s|t1=to pierce through|t2=heart}} instead.
